    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="1183"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1183">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/1933</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Collector of Customs at Los Angeles</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Elliott</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Secretary of Treasury</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_MWG1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">McAdoo</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d1183fn1">Repeated, by telephone, to the
                        Department of State April 6.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Los Angeles</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>British collier <hi rend="italic">Lena</hi>, admittedly a naval tender, arrived
                    to-day San Diego. Master wishes to take on board $1,000 provisions for own crew
                    and $4,000 provisions and large supply of fresh water for vessels salvaging the
                    wrecked Japanese <hi rend="italic">Asama</hi> on coast of Mexico. Also wishes to
                    stay additional 24 hours to make repairs to boiler. This office’s opinion excess
                    supplies may not be taken. Wire instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Elliott</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
